{
  "texts": [
    "This means that we can have both cost (less is better) and benefit (more is better) criteria in one problem.",
    "Formally, in an IDM process one agent needs to choose from a set of options X ¼ fx 1;...; x n g (with n [ 1).",
    "To do so, the agent considers a finite number of characteristics P ¼ fp 1;...; p m g (with m [ 1) of the alternatives.",
    "The degrees of importance of these features may vary.",
    "GDM is different because there is a finite list of agents D ¼ fd 1;...; d k g (with k [ 1)."
  ]
}